# Packaging & configuration

## Three ways to ship code

- **Inline zip** (console) — ≤ 3 MB — tiny utilities
- **Zip via S3** — ≤ 250 MB unzipped — the standard
- **Container image** (OCI) — ≤ 10 GB — big deps, ML, custom runtimes

**Layers** — versioned zips of shared libs/runtimes, mounted in; **≤ 5 per function**, shared across accounts → small packages.

## Config knobs

- **Memory** 128 MB–10 GB — **CPU scales with it** (1 vCPU ≈ 1,769 MB)
- **Timeout** 1 s–15 min — hard cap
- **`/tmp`** 512 MB–10 GB — survives warm invocations
- **Env vars** ≤ 4 KB (KMS-encrypted)

**Key knob:** no CPU dial — **raise memory to get vCPU** for CPU-bound work.
